  <h3>Fitness</h3>

  <p>We by all means accommodate new members but we do expect a certain level of fitness. The natural terrain around us can vary and sometimes the route we may choose may be more challenging for some rides. If you do find that you are struggling with the pace, we advise that you do the first hour and see how you feel. It's better to ride home feeling fine than on your last legs feeling shattered.</p>

  <h3>Equipment</h3>

  <p>Helmets are required, and carry at least one spare inner tube plus a basic tool kit comprising a minimum of:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li>Multi-tool</li>
    <li>Tyre levers</li>
    <li>Chain tool (chain breaker)</li>
    <li>One inner tube (preferably two)</li>
    <li>Spanner (with multiple size holes, helps with brake/pedal situations)</li>
    <li>Spoke key</li>
    <li>Mini pump (or gas canisters and valve)</li>
    <li>An emergency tenner (useful at the cafe stop if nothing else)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>In the Winter months riders should have full length mudguards and preferably a <a href="http://eastyorkshirectc.org.uk/flaps">mudguard flap</a> - it helps to keep our kit clean!</p>

  <p>Our no-drop policy applies to every club ride so there will usually be a tool for the job amongst us somewhere and hands on deck to help out. However, it's still wise to carry a toolkit of your own in case you have to head back home alone for any reason.</p>

  <h3>Insurance</h3>

  <p>We recommend that you are a member of <a href="https://www.britishcycling.org.uk/clubs/membership">British Cycling</a>, they'll provide you with liability insurance for when you're out on a ride.</p>

  <p>Please take time to read our <strong><a href="<%= asset_path('SitwellCyclingClubSitwellCCGenericRiskAssessment–RoadRides2016.pdf') %>">Risk Assessment</a> on Road Riding</strong>.</p>

  <h3>Guide to group riding</h3>

  <p><a href="https://www.britishcycling.org.uk/knowledge/article/izn20121221-group-ride-0">British Cycling</a> has some great information on group riding and even has a guide on hand signals and communication to keep each other safe whilst out on the road. There's also this <a href="<%= asset_path('group-riding-skills-ctc.pdf') %>">handy PDF</a> from CTC that is well worth a look.</p>

